<div id="review_3283206900" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3283206900" />
    <a title="Eric S" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42902277-eric-s"><img alt="Eric S" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3283206900?book_show_action=true">Apr 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric S" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric S" href="/user/show/42902277-eric-s">Eric S</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3283206900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11169278292486790039">This book is a great read for anyone wanting a &quot;popular&quot; book on science. I would rate this a 5 but it is quite dated and so a number of the subjects have moved on since the original writing. With that caveat in mind the reader will find that this is still a fascinating, fast, and factual read. The parts on numbers, basic physics, and other elementary sciences have lost nothing. The author is EXCELLENT at presenting his subject matter. Though he&apos;s not as exuberant as Richard Feynman he&apos;s still v</span>
  <span id="freeText11169278292486790039" style="display:none">This book is a great read for anyone wanting a "popular" book on science. I would rate this a 5 but it is quite dated and so a number of the subjects have moved on since the original writing. With that caveat in mind the reader will find that this is still a fascinating, fast, and factual read. The parts on numbers, basic physics, and other elementary sciences have lost nothing. The author is EXCELLENT at presenting his subject matter. Though he's not as exuberant as Richard Feynman he's still very captivating. I also very much enjoyed how the author would make even dry subjects interesting. A lot of very worthwhile stuff and definitely worth the time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11169278292486790039" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


