<span id="freeTextContainer1409397745037990362">I&apos;m usually right into this sort of book, but I ended up abandoning ~80% of way through. It&apos;s very wide in scope, trying to cover maths, micro- and macro- science. That&apos;s admirable, but I think I prefer to go deep on a single thing. I also didn&apos;t realise it was published in 1947, which combined with breadth and resulting shallowness meant I was already familiar with most of the material.<br/><br/>Feels harsh to give this two stars, since I was sincerely impressed at the scope, but I didn&apos;t finish it so th</span>
  <span id="freeText1409397745037990362" style="display:none">I'm usually right into this sort of book, but I ended up abandoning ~80% of way through. It's very wide in scope, trying to cover maths, micro- and macro- science. That's admirable, but I think I prefer to go deep on a single thing. I also didn't realise it was published in 1947, which combined with breadth and resulting shallowness meant I was already familiar with most of the material.<br /><br />Feels harsh to give this two stars, since I was sincerely impressed at the scope, but I didn't finish it so them the breaks.</span>
